.nh
.TH "BCDOCK" "1" "Jan 2025" "BCDock CLI" "BCDock Manual"

.SH NAME
bcdock-waitlist-join - Submit a waitlist entry non-interactively (CI-friendly)


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbcdock waitlist join [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Submit a waitlist entry without any prompts.

.PP
--name and --email are required; everything else is optional. Unlike
\&'bcdock auth join-waitlist' (interactive), this verb never prompts - it is the
form the smoke suite and other automation drive.

.PP
On the dev mirror with BCDOCK_DEV_TURNSTILE_BYPASS set, the submit clears the
Turnstile gate inline; otherwise it requests the deferred browser-confirm flow
and prints a confirm URL.

.PP
Exit codes:
  0   ok
  1   general error (missing required flag, validation)
  4   rate-limited


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--artifact-type\fP=""
	Default artifact type: Sandbox or OnPrem (optional)

.PP
\fB--bc-version\fP=""
	Default BC version (optional)

.PP
\fB--country\fP=""
	Default BC country code (optional)

.PP
\fB--email\fP=""
	Email address (required)

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for join

.PP
\fB--multi-tenant\fP=""
	true|false - preferred multi-tenant default (optional)

.PP
\fB--name\fP=""
	Your name (required)

.PP
\fB--region\fP=""
	Preferred Azure region (optional)

.PP
\fB--use-case\fP=""
	What you'd like BCDock to help you with (optional)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--api-url\fP=""
	API base URL (env: BCDOCK_API_URL)

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colored output

.PP
\fB-o\fP, \fB--output\fP="table"
	Output format: table, json, csv

.PP
\fB-q\fP, \fB--quiet\fP[=false]
	Suppress non-essential output

.PP
\fB--timeout\fP=30s
	Request timeout

.PP
\fB--token\fP=""
	API token (env: BCDOCK_TOKEN)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  bcdock waitlist join --name "Jane Smith" --email jane@example.com
  bcdock waitlist join --name CI --email "ci+TOKEN.noemail@example.com"
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBbcdock-waitlist(1)\fP
